    Level-1 Your Main Claim: {"claim": "Mandated pseudonymity ultimately harms marginalized communities and hinders genuine social progress.", "argument": ["Mandated pseudonymity can negatively impact marginalized communities.", "Mandated pseudonymity can impede genuine social progress.", "Universal pseudonyms make it harder to build a brand, profit from one's work, and defend against misinterpretations.", "Universal pseudonyms disincentivizes writing, especially on sensitive or personal topics.", "Universal pseudonyms impedes the progress of academic research, limits the creation of art that connects with people on a personal level, and hinders social change driven by powerful storytelling.", "Writing is intellectual property and a form of self-expression.", "Authors deserve the right to tie their name to their creation and benefit from their reputation.", "Universal pseudonyms deny marginalized creators this right, hindering their ability to build a platform and advocate for their communities."]}
